<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-17367] Kafka endpoint DSL for producer doesn&apos;t strip //</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-17367</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m trying something like this&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;.toD(&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
{{ kafka(&quot;my-topic&quot;)}}&lt;br/&gt;
{{ .brokers(&quot;&lt;tt&gt;kafka.brokers&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;)}}&lt;br/&gt;
{{ .partitioner(org.apache.kafka.clients.producer.RoundRobinPartitioner.class.getName())}}&lt;br/&gt;
{{ .valueSerializer(ByteArraySerializer.class.getName()))}}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and I get this error&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Metadata response reported invalid topics &lt;a href=&quot;/my-topic&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;//my-topic&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is because &lt;tt&gt;parseTopicName&lt;/tt&gt; in KafkaSendDynamicAware is unaware of the &lt;tt&gt;//&lt;/tt&gt; in the uri.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
